## ğŸ“‚ Dataset Description

The Maven Hospital Dataset usually consists of multiple tables/files. Example tables include:

### 1ï¸âƒ£ Patients

* `patient_id` â€“ Unique patient identifier
* `first_name`, `last_name` â€“ Patient name
* `gender` â€“ Gender
* `date_of_birth` â€“ Date of birth

### 2ï¸âƒ£ Encounters / Visits

* `encounter_id` â€“ Unique visit identifier
* `patient_id` â€“ Patient ID (FK)
* `admit_date` â€“ Admission date
* `discharge_date` â€“ Discharge date
* `department` â€“ Department (ER, ICU, OPD, etc.)

### 3ï¸âƒ£ Diagnoses

* `diagnosis_id` â€“ Unique diagnosis identifier
* `encounter_id` â€“ Visit ID (FK)
* `diagnosis_code` â€“ Diagnosis code
* `diagnosis_description` â€“ Diagnosis description

### 4ï¸âƒ£ Procedures / Treatments

* `procedure_id` â€“ Unique procedure identifier
* `encounter_id` â€“ Visit ID (FK)
* `procedure_name` â€“ Procedure or treatment name
* `procedure_cost` â€“ Cost of procedure

### 5ï¸âƒ£ Billing / Payments

* `bill_id` â€“ Unique bill identifier
* `encounter_id` â€“ Visit ID (FK)
* `total_charge` â€“ Total charge
* `insurance_coverage` â€“ Insurance coverage amount
* `patient_payment` â€“ Patient payment

> âš ï¸ Note: Table names and column names may vary depending on the dataset version.

